==Hindi==
===Abstract Noun===
'''वहाँ ''' (vahān) <!--nasalization marker would be better than the n-->
# [[there]], but only in the sense of an abstract noun of place. Hindi does not have a word equivalent to the English usage for "there is...".

It is sometimes printed as as [[वहां]] when the full [[w:chandrabindu|chandrabindu]] is not available in the [[typesetting]] system.

